Edit 1 — depth_metrics: accept an optional region mask
Replace the function signature and the valid line (lines 40–48). Add a region parameter and AND it into valid:
Python
@torch.no_grad()
def depth_metrics(pred: torch.Tensor, gt: torch.Tensor,
                  min_d: float = 0.01, max_d: float = 10.0,
                  region: torch.Tensor | None = None) -> dict | None:
    """pred, gt: (1, H, W) metric depth for ONE frame.
    region: optional (1, H, W) or (H, W) bool mask; if given, metrics are
    computed only on pixels inside it (e.g. person masks)."""
    valid = (gt > min_d) & (gt <= max_d)
    if region is not None:
        valid = valid & region.reshape(valid.shape).bool()
    if valid.sum() == 0:
        return None
    p = pred[valid].clamp(min=min_d)
    g = gt[valid]

(The rest of the function — thresh, the return dict(...) — stays exactly as it is.)
Edit 2 — add the --mask argument
After the --use-init-depth argument (line 71), add:
Python
ap.add_argument("--mask", choices=("all", "objects"), default="all",
                    help="'objects' restricts metrics to person-mask pixels")

Edit 3 — build the person-mask region per frame and pass it in
Replace the inner evaluation loop (lines 101–107) with this. It unions the matched instance masks for each frame into one person-region mask, resizes it to the depth resolution, and passes it to depth_metrics:
Python


for b in range(rgb.shape[0]):
                region = None
                if args.mask == "objects":
                    masks = batch["targets"][b].get("masks")        # (G, Hm, Wm) GT person masks
                    if masks is None or masks.numel() == 0:
                        continue                                    # no people in frame -> skip
                    region = masks.to(args.device).any(0, keepdim=True).float()  # (1, Hm, Wm)
                    if region.shape[-2:] != gt[b].shape[-2:]:
                        region = torch.nn.functional.interpolate(
                            region.unsqueeze(0), size=gt[b].shape[-2:], mode="nearest").squeeze(0)
                    region = region > 0.5
                m = depth_metrics(pred[b], gt[b], max_d=max_depth, region=region)
                if m is None:
                    continue
                for k, v in m.items():
                    sums[k] += v
                n += 1

(One detail: this reads batch["targets"][b]["masks"], the GT instance masks your dataset already provides. If your collate stores them under a different key, tell me and I'll adjust — but masks is what the loss used in Phase 2, so it should be right.)
Run all three checkpoints with --mask objects
Bash

export DINOV2_WEIGHTS=/home/work/intern_storage/Ayush/weights/dinov2_vitl14.safetensors
export HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1

python evaluate.py --model-config instancedepth/configs/instance_depth.yaml \
    --data-root gid_custom --checkpoint runs/phase1/ckpt_final.pth \
    --split test --image-size 504 896 --use-init-depth --mask objects --out-json eval_p1_obj.json

python evaluate.py --model-config instancedepth/configs/instance_depth.yaml \
    --data-root gid_custom --checkpoint runs/phase2/ckpt_final.pth \
    --split test --image-size 504 896 --mask objects --out-json eval_p2_obj.json

python evaluate.py --model-config instancedepth/configs/instance_depth.yaml \
    --data-root gid_custom --checkpoint runs/phase3/ckpt_final.pth \
    --split test --image-size 504 896 --mask objects --out-json eval_p3_obj.json

